    / About Section
    %section#about.success
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12.text-center
            %h2 About
            %hr.star-light
        .row
          .col-lg-6
            %h4 About Me:
          .col-lg-6
            %p
              I'm a 3rd year student at the Rochester Institute of Technology.
              I'm studying software engineering with a minor in computer science and communications.
              I have passion for self improvement and I believe that this shows in my work. I've
              taught myself the basics of a web framework (literally) overnight and have spent most
              of my time learning how to learn quicker, faster, and more effectively.
              I have two years experience building web applications for companies in the health domain.
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            %h3 Methodology
          .col-lg-6
            %h4 Agile:
          .col-lg-6
            %p
              I subscribe to the philosophy that it's impossible to know all of the ins and outs of a
              finished project before building it. Because of this I follow an agile methodology allowing
              changes in the design to be easily made. In addition, I use tools to ensure that time
              can be spent developing and fixing issues without worrying about one small change breaking
              and entire ssytem.
        .row
          .col-lg-6
            %img{src: 'img/technique_pomodoro.jpg'}
          .col-lg-6
            %p
              Pomodoros is a form of time management to easily measure out work that can be done by looking
              at previous work. It is a form of time-boxing to see how time can be used most efficiently.
              Because I use this technique, it's very easy to guage how long tasks should take along with
              being able to analyze weak points in my process and make improvements in the future.
        .row
          .col-lg-6
            %h4 IMAGE3
          .col-lg-6
            %p
              If you're looking to hire myself, I can offer competitive rates for a junior software
              engineer and web designer position. I understand what I can (and cannot do) and can
              provide reasonable estimations for my work because of the methods that I use.
          .col-lg-8.col-lg-offset-2.text-center
            %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-outline{:href => "mailto:BryonWilkins94@gmail.com"}
